# Unit tests for update_tool.ml: find_repo_root, git-fail-continue, build-fail-abort

## Requirements

- `update_tool.ml` logic must be testable in isolation without running actual git or make processes
- Tests cover: repo root discovery, git failure handling (non-fatal), build failure handling (fatal/abort), guard when already draining

## Implementation

- File: `test/test_update_tool.ml` (new), `test/dune`
- Use process-injection pattern: pass `~run_git` and `~run_make` as optional parameters (or use a functor/ref) so tests can substitute mock runners
- Test cases:
  1. `find_repo_root`: found (dune-project in parent), not found (returns None), stops at filesystem root
  2. git pull succeeds: output forwarded, build proceeds
  3. git pull exits non-zero: output forwarded with warning, build still proceeds (non-fatal)
  4. make build exits non-zero: error reported, SIGUSR1 NOT sent (fatal)
  5. make build succeeds: "Build complete" message sent, SIGUSR1 triggered
  6. update called while draining=true: returns "Restart already in progress" immediately, no git/make invoked

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 6 test cases pass under `make test`
- [ ] Git failure (non-zero exit) does NOT abort — build step is still invoked
- [ ] Build failure (non-zero exit) does NOT trigger SIGUSR1
- [ ] find_repo_root returns None when no dune-project or .git found
- [ ] make fmt-check passes on new test file
